}}

[[Category:GenericTypePage]]

{{Specific-property-text|i2=3}}


Any of these can be used in the recipes that require a {{PAGENAME}}.

Most can also be used to make [[Leather]]. Exception(s): [[Squirrel Tail]].

Each inventory space that the hide takes up represents 1 {{PAGENAME}}. Hides can be split up into patches by right-clicking them. Hides that take up more inventory spaces than a crafting recipe requires, will be automatically split up and the remainder returned.

==Notes==
*"''Dried hide''" is the shorter alternative name for "''Prepared Animal Hide''" used across the wiki. (''game history related'')
*Some recipes, like the [[Bear Cape]], require a whole hide, so in these cases splitting it up effectively ruins the hide.
*Hide patches cannot be turned into [[leather]].
*Although stacked large-hides can's be manual split inside the stack, they do auto-split when crafting requires it => Mixed Hide+Patch Stack.

